window.docContents[167].resolve({"/Algebraic-Number-Theory/Finiteness-of-the-class-group/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Algebraic-Number-Theory--Finiteness-of-the-class-group--The-Class-Group-Is-Finite":{"contents":"The class group  () of the ring of integers of any number\nfield  is finite.\n\nThe proof bounds the number of ideal classes using Minkowski's geometry-of-numbers bound\n(). mathlib's ClassGroup.fintypeOfAdmissibleOfFinite-style argument\n(specialised to ) shows that every ideal class contains an integral ideal of\nabsolute norm () at most the Minkowski bound\n\nindeed, applying exists_ne_zero_mem_ideal_of_norm_le to a fractional ideal produces a nonzero\nelement of small norm, hence a representative of bounded norm. Since there are only finitely many\nideals of bounded norm (), the class group is represented by\nfinitely many classes, so it is finite.\n\n","context":"AINTLIB — An Atlas of Number Theory in Lean\u0009Algebraic Number Theory\u0009Finiteness of the class group","header":"3.7.1. The Class Group Is Finite","id":"/Algebraic-Number-Theory/Finiteness-of-the-class-group/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Algebraic-Number-Theory--Finiteness-of-the-class-group--The-Class-Group-Is-Finite"},"/Modular-and-Automorphic-Forms/Eisenstein-series/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Modular-and-Automorphic-Forms--Eisenstein-series--Eisenstein-series":{"contents":"For an integer , a positive integer , and a congruence datum\n, the Eisenstein series of weight , level , and\ncharacteristic  is\n\nthe sum running over the integer pairs congruent to  modulo . The normalised Eisenstein\nseries of weight  and level  is the modular form\n\nthe level-one Eisenstein series rescaled to have constant -coefficient .\n\n","context":"AINTLIB — An Atlas of Number Theory in Lean\u0009Modular and Automorphic Forms\u0009Eisenstein series","header":"6.5.1. Eisenstein series","id":"/Modular-and-Automorphic-Forms/Eisenstein-series/#AINTLIB-___-An-Atlas-of-Number-Theory-in-Lean--Modular-and-Automorphic-Forms--Eisenstein-series--Eisenstein-series"}});